Package jetbrains.mps.ide.ui.tree.module

Interface MPSModuleTreeNode

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    GeneratorTreeNode, ModuleTreeNode, ProjectDevKitTreeNode, ProjectLanguageTreeNode, ProjectModuleTreeNode, ProjectSolutionTreeNode, TransientModelsTreeNode
    public interface MPSModuleTreeNode
    Tree node associated with a module. General clients (i.e. tree/UI - actions, menus, editors) can access associated module directly. Clients that need to process modules out-of-process (e.g. validation/error-checking running in a separate thread) shall take care to re-resolve module using SModuleReference, as the tree node might get disposed/invalidated meanwhile. Alternatively, MPSModuleTreeNode might perform resolution itself, and the decision no to do so is deliberate - most clients are of the first kind - resolution would incur performance penalty, and it's unclear how to handle null return value if we resolve it within tree node. evgeny, 6/21/13
